replies.body:
What's the chance of AP Items in general being re-looked at? Right now AP Items feel a bit too "by the book".

You pick your Mana item (with many champions heavily favoring one)
{{item:3165}} {{item:3027}} {{item:3003}} 

You pick your (second) big AP item (since the mana items provide a lot of AP on their own)
{{item:3285}} {{item:3116}} {{item:3089}} 

You pick up your defensive item
{{item:3001}} {{item:3157}} 

You pick up your penetration
{{item:3135}} and {{item:3020}} ({{item:3151}} is only really an option if you got {{item:3116}} earlier)

And you fill in the gaps with either a specialty item or another big AP item
{{item:3100}} {{item:3115}} {{item:3152}} {{item:3198}} 

There's really not a whole lot of customization, the whole process feels more "solved" than Runes or Masteries.
